# Security

Follow [docs/security.md](docs/security.md) and [docs/security/security-review.md](docs/security/security-review.md).

## Never commit

- Database passwords, connection strings with credentials, API keys, JWT secrets
- Real values in `appsettings.json`, `appsettings.Production.json`, `.env`, or deploy configs

Use user secrets (local), Fly secrets (staging/prod), or environment variables.

## Auth (do not weaken)

- SPA: cookie sessions + CSRF on mutating requests
- External/mobile: JWT bearer where documented
- SuperAdmin: TOTP MFA required
- Division-scoped data via `IDivisionScopeService` — no cross-division leaks in new endpoints

## Don't

- Disable `[Authorize]` or module checks to “unblock” development
- Log sensitive fields (passwords, full payment details)
- Copy example credentials from security-review into rules or code
